import './AntiqueTable.css' export default function AntiqueTable({antiques}){ const emptyDefaultList = [{ name:"George", category:"a", value:"b", material:"c", color:"d", style:"e", brand:"f", model:"g", timePeriod:"h", condition:"i", origin:"j", purpose:"k", owner:"l", history:"m", size:"n", comment:"georges comment", }, { name:"Walter", category:"a", value:"b", material:"c", color:"d", style:"e", brand:"f", model:"g", timePeriod:"h", condition:"i", origin:"j", purpose:"k", owner:"l", history:"m", size:"n", comment:"walters comment", }, ] const antiquesList =antiques?.map((antique,index)=>{ const {name,category,value,material,color,size,style,brand,model,timePeriod,condition,origin,purpose,owner,history,comment} = antique; return( {index} {name} {category} {value} {material} {color} {style} {brand} {model} {timePeriod} {condition} {origin} {purpose} {owner} {history} {size} {comment} ) } ) return(
{antiquesList}
Id Name Category Value Material Color Style Brand Model Time Period Condition Origin Purpose Owner History Size Comment Actions
) }
